cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.PL 

The paper discusses a method for agents to learn to act autonomously in real-world domains by acquiring a model of the dynamics of the domain. This involves learning STRIPS action models from noisy and incomplete observations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves learning from data, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of classifiers and transition functions suggests that it could also belong to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on simulated standard planning domains, which suggests that it could belong to cs.PL (Programming Languages).
